quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,15,He has set mountains on the earth - lest it should move away with you. He also made rivers and roads so that you may find your way
  16,16,and likewise made landmarks and the stars for your guidance
  16,17,"Is then, He, Who has created all this, like one who cannot create? Why donâ€™t you understand"
  16,18,"If you want to count the favors of Allah, you will never be able to number them; surely Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  16,19,and Allah knows what you conceal and what you reveal
  16,20,"Those whom they invoke besides Allah have created nothing, but are themselves created"
  16,21,"They are dead, not living; they do not even know when they will be raised to life again"
  16,22,"Your God is One God; as for those who do not believe in the hereafter, they have faithless hearts and are puffed up with arrogance"
  16,23,Allah surely knows what they conceal and what they reveal; certainly He does not love the arrogant
  16,24,"When they are asked: \"What is it, that your Lord has revealed?\" They say: \"Fictitious stories of the ancients"
  16,25,Let them bear their own burden in full and that of those whom they have misled in their ignorance. Alas! Evil is the responsibility they are taking
  16,26,"Those before them also plotted against the Truth, but Allah shook their edifice through its foundation, and its roof caved in on them; and the torment came at them from where they did not even suspect"